review_blob:
Aromatic with deep notes of bourbon, chocolate, malts. Coffee is subtle but present. Divine mouth feel grows in complexity as it warms.  9 out of 10 for the style. Would bang. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Goose Island Bourbon County Stout - Coffee

review_blob:
Incredible nose of cherry, vanilla and bourbon. First sip revealed deep hop levels, slight smoke, chocolate with a smooth velvety finish. Impressive to say the least. Would bang.

Poured a deep brown, short head. Not much for aroma - some coffee. Rich mouth feel, good hop presence throughout. Finishes with espresso hop bitterness, strong notes of dark chocolate. Would definitely buy again.
